CatDescriptText: Mrs. Edward Townes, housewife, 7610 Bennett Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "I believe they will..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mrs. Edward Townes wearing earrings, hat, and light colored gabardine coat, standing in front of painted brick wall with sign on left
